dcDescription: It is often suggested that the distinguishing characteristic of public opinion in contemporary Western societies is a lack of shared moral guidelines in life: everything goes. The only ideal left is what is often called individualism, namely that of not accepting any given roles, values or ideals in life but instead striving towards being as free as possible to behave as one pleases. In the thesis that this chapter forms a part of, I offer a different understanding of the much discussed culture of individualism. In later chapters, I shall present data that allow us to question existing assumptions regarding the empirical nature of individualistic values. In this chapter, however, I begin by addressing what I believe is still an un-settled issue of just as much, if not even more, importance: the concept of individualism and how to define it. This chapter aims to equip us with the theoretical Wellingtons we need before venturing into the empirical swamp of individualism. We still know too little about individualism as a set of moral ideals concerning how human beings and society ought to behave. The root of the problem, I suggest, is that we lack a theoretically sound definition of what this kind of normative individualism is and what it is not; which in turn means we have no existing framework for making systematic comparisons between different versions of individualistic ideals. Here, I develop a definition of normative individualism and such a framework.  In doing so, I do not only contribute to a more thorough understanding of individualism, but also to two closely related debates in political theory. Normative individualism, it is shown, amounts to valuing individual liberty of different kinds. Thus, the concept of individualism provides a new and rewarding entry to two classic conceptual questions which I also discuss: how to define freedom and how to define moral autonomy.
Presented at the Nordic Network in Political Theory, 8th Annual workshop, Uppsala, Sweden, October 2008.

dcDescription: \ ‘Crackòvia\’ opens a new character: Queca, the cuddly sheep of Carles Puyol (Jordi Rios), who can speak and has no hair on his tongue to say what he thinks. Continue\ ‘The comeback of galaxies\’ In this second chapter, the rebel forces are known, with Pep Guardiola (Pep Plaza) in the role of Obi-wan Kenobi, Andres Iniesta (Oriol Cruz) as Luke Skywalker and Carles Puyol (Jordi Rios) playing Princess Leia. Barca players combine to get the back to the league with a spectacular musical based on the mythical theme\ ‘The eye of the tiger\’. Mourinho (Toni Albà) decides to take advantage of Holy Week to continue making himself the martyr in the press room.

dcDescription:
Inventering Sesam 1996-1999:
Förpackning 29 x 15 cm
Figur H 11 cm
Stjärnornas krig-figur, Darth Vader, i originalförpackning. förpackning av svart rektangulär pappskiva med text "STARWARS / RETURN OF THE / JEDI" och bild på Darth Vader. På höger sidan rektangulärt transparent plastfodral (öppnat) i vilken dockan ligger. På baksidan text och bild på 65 st stjärnornas krig-figurer.
Dockan helt gjuten i svart plast, rörliga ben och armar, i vänstra armen är en rosa laserpistol inskjuten som går att skjuta ut. Iklädd lös lång svart kappa av tunn plast. Märkt på vänster lår "c (i ring, copyright-märkt) G.F.G.M.I. 1977".
Leif Wallin 1996
Stjärnornas krig, Darth Vader

Förpackning 29 x 15 cm
Figur H 11 cm


Figuren är från filmerna "Stjärnornas Krig", Darth Vader representerar det onda Kejsardömet. För mer info se inv.nr 312.863-312.868. Dockan inköpt som komplement till Stjärnornas Krig-figurer inköpta i samband med 1986 års hemundersökning SAMDOK.
Serien, som är en science fiction, utspelar sig i rymden där de goda, rebellerna med t ex Han Solo, Prinsessan Leia Organa, Luke Skywalker, Chewbacka the Wookie, R2 D2 (som är en robot) m fl, strider mot de onda, Rymdimperiet, med Darth Wader i spetsen. 
Bilaga
Leif Wallin 1996

Det engelska leksaksföretaget Palitoy sålde Star Wars-figurer på licens från Kenner Toys, som i sin tur fått rättigheterna från Lucasfilm Ltd 1977. Filmen Return of the Jedi utkom 1983.
/Karin Dern 2014
Historisk händelse, person med anknytning till föremålet: Stjärnornas Krig

Inventory Sesam 1996-1999:
Packaging 29 x 15 cm
Figure H 11 cm
The War figure of the Stars, Darth Vader, in original packaging. packaging of black rectangular cardboard with text “STARWARS/RETURN OF THE/JEDI” and image on Darth Vader. On the right side rectangular transparent plastic case (opened) in which the doll lies. On the back text and picture on 65 pcs the stars' war figures.
The doll completely moulded in black plastic, moving legs and arms, in the left arm is a pink laser gun pushed out. Clothed loose long black coat of thin plastic. Marked on the left thigh “c (in ring, copyright labeled) G.F.G.M.I. 1977.”
Leif Wallin 1996
The War of the Stars, Darth Vader

Packaging 29 x 15 cm
Figure H 11 cm


The figure is from the films “The War of the Stars,” Darth Vader represents the evil Empire. For more info see inv.nr 312.863-312.868. The doll purchased as a complement to the Stjärns Krig figures purchased in connection with the 1986 home survey SAMDOK.
The series, which is a science fiction, plays out in space where the good ones, the rebels with Han Solo, Princess Leia Organa, Luke Skywalker, Chewbacka the Wookie, R2 D2 (who is a robot) m fl, contradict the evil ones, the Space empire, with Darth Wader at the forefront. 
Annex
Leif Wallin 1996

The English toy company Palitoy sold Star Wars figures under licence from Kenner Toys, who in turn received the rights from Lucasfilm Ltd in 1977. The film Return of the Jedi appeared in 1983.
Karin Dern 2014
Historical event, person related to the object: War of the Star

dcDescription:
Inventering Sesam 1996-1999:
Rymdskepp i grå plast. Triangelformad, mitt på förarhytt med öppningsbar lucka under vilken det finns 2 säten. (Två Stjärnornas krig-figurer kan placeras där.)  På var sida en lång laserkanon, den högra lös. Bakom förarhytten mörkgrått vridbart harpungevär med lös pil, snöre och en grå kub (vilken troligen har kunnat fästas på batteriluckan). På flera ställen påklistrade originaletiketter i grått och rött/vitt. På bakre högra sidan plats för 2 st 1,5 volts batterier (som har gjort att laserkanonerna har lyst och rymdskeppet låtit), luckan till batteriutrymmet saknas. Under skeppet skjutbar lucka med ett utfällbart grått stöd. (Luckan går nu ej att stänga, stödet löst.) Undertill märkt "c (i ring, copyrightmärke)  LUCAS FILM LTD (LFL) 1980 KENNER PRODUCTIONS CINCINATI, OHIO 45202 No 39610".
Rymdskeppet är tillverkat efter förebild från biofilmen och TV-serien "Stjärnornas Krig" som kom till Sverige från USA i slutet av 1970-talet. Där heter detta rymdskepp "Snowspeed". Space Ships in grey plastic. Triangle shaped, in the middle of a driver’s cab with opening slot under which there are 2 seats. The two stars' war figures can be placed there.) On each side a long laser cannon, the right loose. On the back right side place for 2 pcs 1.5 volts batteries (which have made the laser cannons have shone and the spacecraft sounded), the gap to the battery compartment is missing. Under the ship a sliding hatch with a precipitable grey support. (The Luck is now unable to close, the support resolved.) Underneath marked “c (in ring, copyright mark) LUCAS FILM LTD (LFL) 1980 KENNER PRODUCTIONS CINCINATI, OHIO 45202 No 39610.”

See also inv.nr. 312.864-312.868 and 312.941.
Has belonged to Stefan Stålgärde, Jordbro. Purchased in connection with the 1986 home survey, SAMDOK’s home pool.
Leif Wallin 1996

dcDescription: Das Kinoplakat im gezeichneten Stil von dem dritten Star-Wars-Film „Die Rückkehr der Jedi-Ritter“ ist geprägt von einem farblichen Kontrast zwischen hell und dunkel, symbolisch für den Gut-Böse-Gegensatz. Auf der hellen Seite befinden sich in der Bildmitte die drei Protagonisten: Jedi-Ritter Luke Skywalker (Mark Hamill), Schmuggler Han Solo (Harrison Ford) und Prinzessin Leia Organa (Carrie Fisher). Die dunkle Seite des Plakats wird von dem ikonischen Helm des Antagonisten Darth Vader (David Prowse) eingenommen. Rundherum sind weitere Figuren und Handlungsorte des Films abgebildet. Ideengeber George Lucas verarbeitete in der ursprünglichen Star-Wars-Saga verschiedene Mythen und Filmklassiker. Aber auch Referenzen zu Geschichte und Zeitgeschehen – wie etwa Massenvernichtungswaffen oder der Vietnamkrieg – wurden genutzt. Wie seine beiden Vorgänger war „Die Rückkehr der Jedi-Ritter“ an den Kinokassen überaus erfolgreich und zog allein in der BRD mehr als fünf Millionen Zuschauer*innen an. Neben Filmen wurde Star-Wars vor allem durch Merchandise fester Bestandteil der modernen Popkultur.
